        <div class="content-card">
            <h1>How to change user agent in Feedzy</h1>

            <p>User-agent tells you about the browser and operating system being used by the particular device so that the website can customize the content accordingly. It is contained in the HTTP headers. Suppose you want to see how the content of your website will be customized according to the device you want to specify, you can always change it.</p>

            <div class="step-header">1</div>
            <div class="step-content">
                To change the user agent, navigate to <strong>Feedzy RSS > Settings</strong>.
            </div>

            <div class="step-header">2</div>
            <div class="step-content">
                Switch to the <strong>Headers</strong> tab and paste the <strong>user agent</strong> string. <strong>Here</strong> is the list of all available user agents.
